<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>df -h shows /dev/sda1 (my root partition) to be using 41Gigs.</p> <p>ncdu / shows my filesystem using 15-16 Gigs.</p> <p>Where does the difference come from? I&#39;m pretty sure I didn&#39;t download/install any heavy games/movies.</p> <p>&#x200B;</p> <p>d f -h output --&gt; <a href="https://ibb.co/zNCRhd0">https://ibb.co/zNCRhd0</a></p> <p>ncdu output --&gt; <a href="https://ibb.co/wcBNLJT">https://ibb.co/wcBNLJT</a></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/MrHyd3_"> /u/MrHyd3_ </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w4puti/df_shows_disk_fuller_then_it_is/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w4puti/df_shows_disk_fuller_then_it_is/">[comments]</a></span>